    http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4

    ValueWithAttributes DateEffectiveExpire

      • http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4:DateEffectiveExpire

      • Description

        Used to identify the effective date and/or expiration date.

    • Example XML

      <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>

<DateEffectiveExpire effective="2011-01-24" expire="2011-07-04" expireDateExclusiveInd="true" xmlns="http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4"/>

      Example JSON

      {
  "DateEffectiveExpire" : {
    "value" : null,
    "effective" : "2011-01-24",
    "expire" : "2011-07-04",
    "expireDateExclusiveInd" : true
  }
}

      • Attribute Summary

        Attributes 
        Name Description
        effective
        Indicates the starting date.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:date
        Example Value 2011-01-24
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        expire
        Indicates the ending date.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:date
        Example Value 2011-01-24
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1

      • Indicator Summary

        Indicators 
        Name Description
        expireDateExclusiveInd
        When true, indicates that the ExpireDate is the first day after the applicable period (e.g. when expire date is Oct 15 the last date of the period is Oct 14).
